{"id": "duc04-testb-38:5#16", "contents": "Lebanese officials have vehemently denied the presence of Kurdish rebels in their country. Foreign Minister Faris Bweiz stated that Turkey is aware that measures were taken in Syria and Lebanon over a year ago to halt the activities of any PKK members. Bweiz emphasized Lebanon's support for Syria, particularly in its call for resolving disputes with Turkey through peaceful dialogue. This stance was echoed by Prime Minister Rafik Hariri, who attributed Turkey's military actions to its recent military alliance with Israel."}
